{
  "texts": [
    "A few stellar sources do have large differences between the parameter values of multiple measurements, which might be owing to accidentally wrong pointing of telescope fibers.",
    "In order to recognize the objects with consistent stellar atmospheric parameters between multiple measurements, we define the deviation of one measurement, which is the absolute difference between the parameter value of the measurement and the source parameter value defined in Equation (1).",
    "For example, for the multiple measurements of effective temperature of a stellar source, {T i eff, i = 1,",
    "• • •, N obs }, the deviation of the ith measurement (denoted by |∆T i eff |) is defined as |∆T i eff | = |T i eff -T eff, source |.",
    "The deviations |∆ log g i | and |∆[Fe/H] i | can be defined similarly."
  ]
}